msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:506
msgid "When does the expiry action occur?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:507
msgid "Post expiry is processed by WordPress scheduled events (cron). The action will occur shortly after the expiry date and time passes. The exact timing depends on your site traffic and WordPress cron configuration."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:509
msgid "Can I disable expiry for a specific post?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:510
msgid "Yes. Simply leave the expiry date and time fields empty in the Post Expiry metabox."
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:512
msgid "How do Smart Rules work with per-post overrides?"
msgstr ""

#: includes/class-msc-post-expiry-settings.php:513
msgid "When a post expires, the plugin checks Smart Rules first. If a rule matches the post, its action is used. If no rules match, the per-post action override is checked. If neither exists, the global default action is applied."
msgstr ""

